reviews.text: Have eaten from stall for many years at Choa Chu Kang Ave 1 Blk 253A,food standard and taste still the same but prices have increased( understandable due to raw ingredients prices have increased),I also buy the whole spring chicken or half spring chicken with rice,chicken cutlet.Will try other  items at time.

Old school western food like many say. Old charm. Tastes Old school. Really bring back good memories of eating comfort western food. Delicious and affordable too in today's time and price. Worthy to eat once in awhile because the food is greasy good. Fried chicken, butter rice, fries, chicken chop, wings, steak and their packet chili are reminiscent of the good old 90s.

Ordered the chicken cutlet set.old school flavourful.crispy with salad sides fries n baked beans.with a small  bun that is freshly fried on the spot.Reasonable price.Old Couples were very friendly.will come again for other sets.

It's within the coffee shop, so there isn't much atmosphere. Lots of people ordering but waiting time isn't too long. About 15mins.
Cutlet portion looks ok but it seems that there's more flour than chicken.
But the taste is good. The old-school western food.
Childhood go to place for hearty western food that is generous and yummy and LEMAKKKKK not for the calorie conscious dinner haha, this is really oily goodie to the max!
